# TURN server for online play. Online games connect peer-to-peer over WebRTC;
# STUN (built in) is enough on many networks, but players behind strict/symmetric
# NATs — or two tabs on a machine that hides local IPs behind mDNS — need a TURN
# relay. There is no reliable free public TURN, so bring your own (Metered, Twilio
# and ExpressTURN all have free tiers).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and fill in your credentials, then
# rebuild. These values are bundled into the client and visible to users, which is
# normal for TURN — prefer a provider that scopes or expires credentials.
#
# Comma-separate multiple URLs that share one username/credential.
VITE_TURN_URLS=turn:your-turn-host:3478,turn:your-turn-host:443?transport=tcp
VITE_TURN_USERNAME=your-username
VITE_TURN_CREDENTIAL=your-credential
